{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9d7d8506-36e2-45c9-90be-0a2c10f3e8bf","content":"The migration is straightforward. In your project file, make these two changes:\n\n**1. Remove (or set to `false`) the VSTest flag:**\n\n```xml\n<!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\n**2. Keep your SDK reference as-is:**\n\n```xml\n<Sdk Name=\"MSTest.Sdk\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n```\n\nMSTest.Sdk **3.8.0** defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is not explicitly set to `true`, so simply removing that property is enough.\n\n**Other things to check:**\n\n- **CLI change:** Use `dotnet test` as before (supported), but you can also run the test executable directly.\n- **`[TestMethod]` / `[TestClass]`** — no changes needed; the test authoring model is the same.\n- **Runsettings:** Most `.runsettings` options carry over, but review any VSTest-specific adapter settings.\n- **CI pipelines:** If you rely on `--logger trx`, replace with `--report-trx` (the new platform flag). Check any other `--` CLI arguments against the [new CLI options](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform-overview).\n- **Extensions:** If you use custom VSTest adapters/extensions, verify they have Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"50974d5a-26b9-4ca6-b9c2-ccccd6bcac14","outputTokens":338,"requestId":"A033:2C9D9E:C06F0D:E15988:69FE86A0"},"id":"1fce2e90-db34-4ca8-8acc-a04886cc5921","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:58:18.199Z","parentId":"c1047c95-9c85-4c76-b6fa-64f39c61984a"}
